---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Collapsible from '../components/Collapsible.astro';
import Sidenote from '../components/Sidenote.astro';
import HoverCard from '../components/HoverCard.astro';
import Window from '../components/Window.astro';
import WindowManager from '../components/WindowManager.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Paul Diaz Ashot"
	description="Founder-operator. Founding team at GMX. Active AI developer using Claude Code, Codex CLI, and GPT-5.5. London, Barcelona, New York."
>
	<main class="cv">
		<header class="cv-header">
			<h1>Paul Diaz Ashot</h1>
			<div class="locations">London, Barcelona, New York</div>
			<div class="contact">
				<a href="mailto:paul.ashot@icloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">paul.ashot@icloud.com</a> ·
				(646) 996 5037 ·
				<a href="https://pauldiazashot.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pauldiazashot.com</a> ·
				@supersonicsines
			</div>
		</header>

		<div class="cv-body">
			<Collapsible title="Introduction">
				<p>
					I am a founder-operator. I have been selling since I was 12. First it was paintings, now it's ideas. I spent four years on the founding team of <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-gmx" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>GMX</b></button>, where I handled go-to-market and onboarded major partners. I spent four years running a venture consultancy practice alongside and after it, where I helped portfolio companies raise funding and pivot strategies to become profitable. My current obsession is deploying AI agents with the best model for each job, from Claude to GPT-5.5, to automate and scale real businesses such as Pawlymarket and Slashwork. Native English, fluent Russian, fluent Spanish; <Sidenote id="right-to-work" term="right to work in the UK, US, and EU">UK indefinite leave to remain status holder + US/EU dual national.</Sidenote>.
				</p>
				<p>
					This is a hypertextual page, underlined items can be interacted with for additional context and information. The PDF version is
					<a href="/Paul_Diaz_Ashot_CV.pdf" download target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
				</p>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Experience">
				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="portico" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>Portico Ventures</b> — <em>Managing Partner</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2021 – 2026</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Venture capital fund specialising in advising and investing in early stage DeFi/Fintech.
						Worked closely on GTM with several portfolio companies including <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-gammaswap" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Gammaswap</b></button>
						and <button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-codex" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Codex.io</b></button>.
						Influenced <b>$4M+ in aggregate fundraising</b> through advisory work and warm introductions.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="gmx" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>GMX</b> — <em>Founding Team · Growth &amp; Partnerships</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2020 – 2023</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Three-person founding team. Top DeFi revenue generator during my tenure.
						Co-led institutional partnerships and capital formation; personally sourced
						<b>$20M+ in cumulative capital deployments</b>.
					</li>
					<li>
						Closed and co-closed strategic partnerships with <Sidenote id="arbitrum" term="Arbitrum" italic>Arbitrum is an L2 for Ethereum that GMX utilised for lower transaction costs. Part of being an early adopter was negotiating for grants and trader rebates worth $10M+. <a href="https://gmxio.substack.com/p/how-gmx-will-utilise-the-12-million" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the GMX Arbitrum incentive post</a>.</Sidenote>, <Sidenote id="avalanche" term="Avalanche" italic>The Avalanche Rush deployment incentive was one of the biggest incentive packages secured in DeFi at the time. The $4M in trading rewards led to eight-figure increases in TVL within a few months. <a href="https://medium.com/avalancheavax/gmx-joins-avalanche-rush-with-4m-in-trading-rewards-ce5c66f0e3b3" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the Avalanche Rush announcement</a>.</Sidenote>, <em>Chainlink</em>, and <em>Frax</em>, plus two other protocol integrations. Coordinated the <HoverCard term="Gambit → GMX rebrand">
							<span class="hc-p">The rebrand wasn't a marketing exercise; it was a chain migration from BSC (Gambit) to <em>Arbitrum</em> and <em>Avalanche</em> (GMX), with the partner network lined up to launch alongside.</span>
							<span class="hc-p">Gambit was initially successful on BSC, reaching nine-figure TVL and issuing GUSDT, a stablecoin backed by aggregate long/short position float and funding fees. The product was thoughtful, but market volatility broke the peg, so the migration demanded a technical rethink rather than a cosmetic rename.</span>
							<span class="hc-p">My role as de facto community lead was to move users into a new product on new chains without fracturing the community after losses in the first system. It worked: users who held through the migration saw 500%+ ROI, and the Telegram community largely stayed intact through the transition.</span>
						</HoverCard> and organised outreach to future partners.
					</li>
					<li>
						Built and led the institutional and community channels: <b>5,000+ Telegram members</b> and direct relationships with eight-figure liquidity providers.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<div class="role-title">
						<HoverCard term="Effie Perine LTD.">
							<span class="hc-p">Effie Perine is a dealership and consignment business run by my brother, Alexis Ashot, a world-class expert in Dutch Pictures.</span>
							<span class="hc-p">My work there extended my first exposure to selling antiques and paintings as a child. During that period I learned the importance of client relationships, building and maintaining good deal flow, sourcing leads, and managing risk in highly seasonal businesses.</span>
							<span class="hc-p">It was a brief transition from education into professional life, but it laid the foundation for many of the commercial habits I later used in crypto, venture advisory, and AI deployments.</span>
						</HoverCard> — <em>Operations &amp; Client Relations</em>
					</div>
					<div class="dates">2019 – 2020</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Managed financial accounts and operational administration for a private art dealership specialising in Old Master Pictures; annual transaction volumes in the £500K–£2.5M+ range.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Current AI Deployments">
				<ul>
					<li>
						<button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="preview-slashwork" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Slashwork.xyz</b></button> — fully live, free AI-deployed job-search engine for the startup and technical community, focused on fresh roles at tracked public-market companies. Built end-to-end with Claude Opus.
					</li>
					<li>
						<button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="pawlymarket" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Pawlymarket</b></button> — live scraper and data aggregator using statistical models to identify market inefficiencies. <b>$50K ARR</b> within two months of launch. <a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a>.
					</li>
					<li>
						<button type="button" class="inline-preview-trigger" data-window-trigger="vinted" aria-haspopup="dialog"><b>Vinted-to-Depop reselling agent</b></button> — autonomous fashion-arbitrage system operating across Vinted and Depop.
					</li>
					<li>
						<Sidenote id="booking" term="Intelligent booking system">A Barcelona dance school with 100+ weekly individual bookings moved onto an AI-coded management and analytics system built with Claude Code and Codex CLI. The agent tracks seasonality across evening vs afternoon classes, Salsa vs Bachata, and experience level, then suggests schedules from basic regression and heuristics. Estimated admin efficiency increased about 50%.</Sidenote> — Codex CLI-assisted agentic scheduler for a small local business; takes class bookings and organises future classes based on predicted demand.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Education" open={false}>
				<p>
					<b>BSc Chemistry</b>, <em>University of Manchester</em>, 2018.
				</p>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Skills" open={false}>
				<p class="skills">
					Consultative selling to technical buyers · enterprise negotiation · founder-network leverage · community-led growth · technical product evangelism · venture capital · startup operations · risk management · market intelligence · financial modelling · ATS scraping · SQLite/FTS · Claude API · Claude Code · Codex CLI · GPT-5.5 · prompt engineering · agentic workflows · MCP · Python · JavaScript
				</p>
			</Collapsible>
		</div>

		<footer class="cv-footer">
			<a href="mailto:paul.ashot@icloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">paul.ashot@icloud.com</a> ·
			@supersonicsines ·
			<a href="/Paul_Diaz_Ashot_CV.pdf" download target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download CV (PDF)</a>
		</footer>
	</main>

	<!-- External preview windows -->
	<Window
		id="preview-gmx"
		title="https://gmx.io"
		initialX={154}
		initialY={96}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/gmx-preview-1280.png" width="1280" height="720" alt="Preview of https://gmx.io" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://gmx.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://gmx.io">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<Window
		id="preview-gammaswap"
		title="https://gammaswap.com"
		initialX={176}
		initialY={112}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/gammaswap-preview-1280.png" width="1280" height="720" alt="Preview of https://gammaswap.com" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://gammaswap.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://gammaswap.com">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<Window
		id="preview-slashwork"
		title="https://slashwork.xyz"
		initialX={188}
		initialY={128}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/slashwork-preview-1280.png" width="1280" height="720" alt="Preview of https://slashwork.xyz" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://slashwork.xyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://slashwork.xyz">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<Window
		id="preview-codex"
		title="https://www.codex.io"
		initialX={220}
		initialY={144}
		initialWidth={640}
		initialHeight={388}
		resizable={false}
		variant="preview"
	>
		<div class="external-preview">
			<img src="/previews/codex-preview-1280.png" width="1280" height="720" alt="Preview of https://www.codex.io" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
			<a class="external-preview-arrow" href="https://www.codex.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open https://www.codex.io">→</a>
		</div>
	</Window>

	<!-- Role windows -->
	<Window id="portico" title="Portico Ventures · Managing Partner" initialX={140} initialY={100}>
		<p><b>Portico Ventures</b> — <em>Managing Partner, 2021 – 2026</em></p>
		<p>
			Portico Ventures was a boutique fund built around accelerator and
			consultancy work for DeFi and fintech companies.
		</p>
		<p>
			The partnership had seven managing partners from different backgrounds, with
			specialisations across engineering, finance, marketing, and distribution. I
			usually worked with consumer-facing products where distribution and
			product-market fit mattered most.
		</p>
		<p>
			My strongest contributions were around diagnosing demand, closing distribution
			deals, sharpening founder narratives, and helping technical products reach
			clearer buyers. Across the portfolio, Portico backed 20 companies, recorded
			six exits, and reached eight-figure peak AUM.
		</p>
	</Window>

	<Window id="gmx" title="GMX · Founding Team · Growth & Partnerships" initialX={200} initialY={140} initialWidth={580}>
		<p><b>GMX</b> — <em>Founding Team · Growth &amp; Partnerships, 2020 – 2023</em></p>
		<p>
			Working on GMX was a labour of love in a ruthless, high-pressure
			environment where execution failures or exploits could permanently damage
			your reputation.
		</p>
		<p>
			As a decentralised perps exchange, we were not just pioneers. We were
			operating in regulatory uncertainty, launching in the first year of a new US
			presidency during intense scrutiny for DeFi.
		</p>
		<p>
			The work matched my skill set and interests more than anything I had done
			before. I built lifelong relationships there, and the biggest personal lesson
			was how rewarding I find the front line of a technological space: users
			asking hard questions, partners needing conviction, liquidity providers
			weighing risk, and a product whose credibility had to be earned in public.
		</p>
	</Window>

	<!-- Current deployment windows -->
	<Window id="pawlymarket" title="Pawlymarket · Prediction-Market Analytics" initialX={236} initialY={108} initialWidth={820} initialHeight={650}>
		<p><b>Pawlymarket</b> — <em>decentralised quantitative-analysis community for Polymarket</em></p>
		<p>
			A members' room built over Polymarket. The engine runs statistical regression on
			the full live order book, AI curates the survivors, and members assemble hedges
			against the curated pairs to extract yield from mispriced beta. Closer to a small
			quant desk than another arbitrage bot.
		</p>
		<div class="window-media window-media--sixty-five">
			<img src="/images/cv/pawlymarket-dashboard-1280-rgb.png" width="1280" height="1025" alt="Pawlymarket explorer showing curated market pairs, correlation scores, and chart controls" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
		</div>
		<p>
			Every five minutes, the analyzer refreshes Polymarket and ranks viable pairs by
			correlation, beta, cointegration, half-life, and volume. Rules, AI categorization,
			and a written macro thesis narrow that universe to roughly 250 live pairs,
			grouped as dead-market, theta, negative-beta, partial-beta, or drift signals.
			The edge is spread reconvergence, not directional betting.
		</p>
		<p>
			The product ships signals through Telegram, web alerts, and an Explorer with
			charts, outcome models, saved pairs, member-submitted pair discussions, and wallet
			tracking for top Polymarket accounts on Polygon CTF.
		</p>
		<p>
			Built end-to-end on Claude Code and Codex CLI. Haiku, Sonnet, Opus, and GPT-5.5
			each run the part of the workflow where they are strongest. Wallet-connect auth,
			USDC/USDT on Polygon, no KYC.
			<a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a>
		</p>
	</Window>

	<Window id="vinted" title="Vinted → Depop · Reselling Agent" initialX={300} initialY={124} initialWidth={640} initialHeight={560}>
		<p><b>Vinted-to-Depop reselling agent</b> — <em>autonomous fashion arbitrage</em></p>
		<p>
			End-to-end autonomous fashion-arbitrage agent operating across Vinted and Depop.
			It manages inventory, makes purchases, pushes listings, and sends final shipment
			review to the end user via Telegram.
		</p>
		<div class="window-media window-media--seventy-five">
			<img src="/images/cv/vinted-depop-glitter-1100-rgb.png" width="1100" height="701" alt="Glitter Vinted intelligence platform terminal interface" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
		</div>
		<p>
			The agent is driven by a multipass Haiku, Opus, and GPT-5.5 flow running through a
			terminal interface. Seeded with $10K, it generated $25K in six months, averaging
			close to 100% returns per item with a sub-10% loss rate.
		</p>
	</Window>

	<WindowManager />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.cv {
		max-width: 680px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 48px 24px;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		counter-reset: sidenote;
	}

	.cv-header,
	.cv-body,
	.cv-footer {
		max-width: 680px;
	}

	.cv-header {
		text-align: center;
		padding-bottom: 14px;
		border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--color-rule);
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.cv-header h1 {
		margin: 0 0 8px 0;
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 400;
		letter-spacing: 1.5px;
	}

	.locations {
		font-size: 15px;
		color: var(--color-ink);
		margin-bottom: 6px;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.contact {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 12px;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		margin-bottom: 4px;
	}

	.contact a {
		color: var(--color-ink);
	}

	.role {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: baseline;
		margin: 12px 0 4px 0;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 4px;
	}

	.role-trigger {
		all: unset;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: var(--color-ink);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-rule);
		text-underline-offset: 3px;
		text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
		transition: text-decoration-thickness 120ms ease-out;
	}

	.role-trigger:hover,
	.role-trigger:focus-visible {
		text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-ink);
	}

	.role-trigger:focus-visible {
		outline: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
		outline-offset: 4px;
	}

	.role-title {
		font-size: 15px;
		color: var(--color-ink);
	}

	.inline-preview-trigger {
		all: unset;
		cursor: pointer;
		color: var(--color-ink);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-rule);
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
		text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
		transition:
			text-decoration-color 120ms ease-out,
			text-decoration-thickness 120ms ease-out;
	}

	.inline-preview-trigger:hover,
	.inline-preview-trigger:focus-visible {
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-ink);
		text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
	}

	.inline-preview-trigger:focus-visible {
		outline: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
		outline-offset: 3px;
	}

	.role .dates {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 12px;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		font-style: italic;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.cv :global(p),
	.cv :global(li) {
		font-size: 15px;
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin: 0 0 6px 0;
	}

	.cv :global(ul) {
		margin: 4px 0 10px 0;
		padding-left: 16px;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.cv :global(li) {
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 14px;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	.cv :global(li::before) {
		content: "–";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--color-ink);
	}

	.cv :global(a) {
		color: var(--color-ink);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-decoration-color: var(--color-rule);
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
	}

	.cv :global(em) {
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.cv :global(b) {
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.external-preview {
		position: relative;
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		min-height: 0;
		overflow: hidden;
		background:
			linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(251, 250, 247, 0.08), rgba(61, 43, 31, 0.2)),
			#17110d;
	}

	.external-preview img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		object-fit: cover;
		filter: saturate(0.88) contrast(0.96);
	}

	.external-preview::after {
		content: "";
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		border: 1px solid rgba(251, 250, 247, 0.16);
		pointer-events: none;
	}

	.external-preview .external-preview-arrow {
		position: absolute;
		right: 26px;
		top: 50%;
		transform: translateY(-52%);
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 132px;
		height: 132px;
		color: rgba(251, 250, 247, 0.44);
		font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
		font-size: 122px;
		font-weight: 400;
		line-height: 1;
		text-decoration: none;
		text-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(23, 17, 13, 0.42);
		transition:
			color 140ms ease-out,
			text-shadow 140ms ease-out,
			transform 140ms ease-out;
	}

	.external-preview .external-preview-arrow:hover,
	.external-preview .external-preview-arrow:focus-visible {
		color: rgba(251, 250, 247, 0.92);
		text-shadow: 0 2px 18px rgba(23, 17, 13, 0.74);
		transform: translateY(-52%) translateX(2px);
		outline: none;
	}

	:global(.mobile-window-inline-content) .external-preview {
		height: auto;
		aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
	}

	:global(.mobile-window-inline-content) .external-preview .external-preview-arrow {
		right: 12px;
		width: 84px;
		height: 84px;
		font-size: 76px;
	}

	.skills {
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	.cv-footer {
		margin: 32px auto 0 auto;
		padding-top: 16px;
		border-top: 0.5px solid var(--color-rule);
		text-align: center;
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 12px;
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}

	.cv-footer a {
		color: var(--color-ink);
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.cv {
			padding: 32px 20px;
		}

		.role {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 2px;
		}

		.role .dates {
			font-size: 11px;
		}
	}
</style>
